PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has ordered the reorganisation of the operational strategies of Nigeria’s security network. The President said Nigerians had lost confidence in the security sector and that he was ready to restore that confidence. The National Security Adviser, Maj. Gen. Babagana Monguno (retd), disclosed this to State House correspondents on Tuesday, after the National Security Council meeting, chaired by the President. The NSA said Buhari expressed worry over the worsening security situation in the country, and had resolved to overhaul the country’s security framework. According to him, the President reiterated his last order to the security chiefs that their best was not good enough. More later… 